<br>
Here's a good example:<br>
<br>
I'm killing Vamps in Tenebrous mountiains. I started off quading them after I had killed a couple and figured out how weak they are (for me at my level). So, after about two weeks of having my exp split 70/30 I decided to go 100% to AA yesterday. I got from 1.5 yellows in AA to my next point in 11 hours. It took me almost 4 months to get out of 51 though. I didn't quad at 51. That was a long time ago, and I didn't usually didn't have the mana then like I do now. Plus I have a familiar, which is nice. Didn't have that then either <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/ukaedir.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Kaedir</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(12/30/01 2:07:53 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Question about alt advancement</span><hr size=1> im lvl 51, im quading in CS atm, one day i wanted to see how much AA exp. i would get quading wit 100% AA exp. up, so i did it and i got a full blue, i was really surprised, i had C2 so i managed to get an orange of AA exp. in about 30-40 min. now what i do is set regular exp. 100%, then wait till i get 2 and a half blues, then i set it to 100% AA exp. and i get a full orange, then back to regular, then back to 100% AA, rinse, repeat. works out nicely, gonna try and get baron title before 55 <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  suggest some of u quading wizzies at around my level try it out.<br>
